primary_diagnosis.description: Major depressive disorder, recurrent, moderate episode
primary_diagnosis.justification: Clinical history confirms multiple prior episodes of depression without any reported manic or hypomanic features, supporting a recurrent unipolar course. The current episode is impacting function and warranted intervention (*Sertraline* initiation 4 weeks ago), establishing the severity as moderate.
dsm_criteria_met: Meets criteria for Major Depressive Episode (5 or more symptoms present during the same 2-week period, including depressed mood and/or anhedonia).
Has had at least one previous Major Depressive Episode.
No history of Manic or Hypomanic episodes (Rules out Bipolar Disorder).

ruled_out.reason: The patient explicitly denies any history of manic or hypomanic episodes, consistent with the Clinical Entity Agent's determination of Recurrent Major Depressive Disorder.

ruled_out.description: Major depressive disorder, single episode, moderate
ruled_out.reason: Clinical history indicates previous episodes, ruling out a single episode designation.
